As another example, 

US Patent 5,766,886 to Studnicka et al., issued June 16, 1998

 ("Modified antibody variable domains") describes methods for identifying the amino acid residues of an antibody variable domain which may be modified without diminishing the native affinity of the antigen binding domain while reducing its immunogenicity with respect to a heterologous species and methods for preparing these modified antibody variable domains which are useful for administration to heterologous species. See also 

